solaris share
command

1. sharemgr list -v
view the group’s properties

2. sharemgr show -v
view shares

3. sharemgr show -vp
view shares with properties
->
default nfs=()
zfs
build nfs=(anon="0,ro=@192.168.1.0/24")
          /bits/provisioning    "Build infrastructure"
 
 
4. add share group
ex:
sharemgr create homegroup
sharemgr show -vp
->
group1 nfs=() smb=()
ex:
sharemgr create -P nfs build
create group build 
sharemgr list -v
->
default enabled nfs
zfs enabled
build enabled nfs

5. add share dir to share group
sharemgr add-share -s /bits/provisioning -d “Build infrastructure” build
sharemgr show -v
->
default
zfs
build
          /bits/provisioning    "Build infrastructure"
		  
6. set properties for share group
sharemgr set -P nfs -p anon=0,ro=@192.168.1.0/24 build
